                            <comment id="17311656" author="emilles" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2021 17:16:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you also consider &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8659&quot; title=&quot;Base class has final getter; extending class has property of same name; no warning for final override&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8659&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8659&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; if making any clarifications in documentation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17311847" author="paulk" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2021 23:05:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt; So far the doco clarifications haven&apos;t touched upon inheritance. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8659&quot; title=&quot;Base class has final getter; extending class has property of same name; no warning for final override&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8659&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8659&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is certainly something which needs further work. It probably belongs as a separate PR - it may even require breaking code changes for some edge cases. We should at least check that the direction we want to head for that is compatible with the changes for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17312896" author="paulk" created="Thu, 1 Apr 2021 06:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed PR merged.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17312950" author="paulk" created="Thu, 1 Apr 2021 07:29:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt;&#160;I fixed up the doco as per current behavior and guidelines for using the existing behavior. There is a breaking change we could do on that issue that would eliminate some current behavior which many might find puzzling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
